%description:
Tests IPv6 PIM-DM (RFC 3973) flood-and-prune over IPv6.

Topology (all links are Ethernet point-to-point):

                       recv
                        |
    source -- R1 -- R2 -+
               |
               +-- R3 -- idleHost

The source behind R1 sends UDP datagrams to the global-scope IPv6 multicast
group ff0e::1 (hop limit > 1). All three routers run PIM-DM over IPv6
(addressFamily "ipv6") and form PIM neighborships with Hellos sourced from their
link-local addresses. recv (behind R2) is an MLD listener of ff0e::1; idleHost
(behind R3) never joins.

Expected PIM-DM behavior:
  - recv RECEIVES the stream: R1 floods to R2 and R3; R2 has a connected receiver
    (learned via MLD -> ipv6MulticastGroupRegistered -> PIM "receiver added"),
    so the (S,G) tree forwards end-to-end to recv.
  - R3 floods the first datagram, finds no receiver (its only downstream is
    idleHost, which never joined), so its outgoing interface list becomes null
    and R3 sends a Prune(S,G) upstream to R1. The R1->R3 branch stops forwarding
    and idleHost receives nothing.

This exercises, over IPv6: PIM neighbor discovery on link-local addresses, the
MLD-driven receiver-added event (the ipv6MulticastGroupRegistered signal now
emitted by Ipv6InterfaceData), flood-and-forward end-to-end delivery, and an
explicit upstream Prune of a branch with no receiver.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ipv6.MulticastRouter6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network PimDmTest6
{
    types:
        channel ethernetline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        source: StandardHost6;
        R1: MulticastRouter6;
        R2: MulticastRouter6;
        R3: MulticastRouter6;
        recv: StandardHost6;
        idleHost: StandardHost6;
    connections:
        source.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> R1.ethg++;
        R1.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> R2.ethg++;
        R1.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> R3.ethg++;
        R2.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> recv.ethg++;
        R3.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> idleHost.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = PimDmTest6
sim-time-limit = 60s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "
ned-path = .;../../../../src

#omnetpp 5.0 - 5.1 compatibility:
eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# All PIM interfaces run in dense mode.
**.pimConfig = xml("<config><interface mode=\"dense\"/></config>")

# MLD on every node (hosts become listeners; routers learn local membership).
**.ipv6.hasMld = true

# Fast deterministic startup: skip Duplicate Address Detection.
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

# source: send to the IPv6 group ff0e::1 with hop limit > 1 so routers forward.
*.source.numApps = 1
*.source.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
*.source.app[0].destAddresses = "ff0e::1"
*.source.app[0].destPort = 1000
*.source.app[0].messageLength = 64B
*.source.app[0].timeToLive = 10
*.source.app[0].startTime = 20s
*.source.app[0].sendInterval = 1s
*.source.app[0].stopTime = 29.5s    # sends at t=20s..29s -> 10 packets

# recv: persistent MLD listener of ff0e::1 behind R2; must receive the stream.
*.recv.numApps = 1
*.recv.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
*.recv.app[0].localPort = 1000
*.recv.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1"

# idleHost: never joins -> its branch is pruned and it receives nothing.
*.idleHost.numApps = 1
*.idleHost.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
*.idleHost.app[0].localPort = 1000

# Ethernet queues
**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 100

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the receiver behind R2 must receive all 10 datagrams (flood-and-forward works end-to-end)
%contains: stdout
recv.app[0]: received 10 packets
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the branch with no listener must be pruned (R1 sends a Prune on the idleHost interface)
%contains: stdout
Sending Prune(S=
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# PIM neighbors are learned on their link-local addresses (RFC 7761)
%contains: stdout
Received PIM Hello from neighbor: interface=eth1 address=fe80:
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
